## Context
Wave-1 move of the code reorg epic (tracker `0240`). Relocate the Phase-2
analysis **entry points** — `analyze_*`, `compute_*`, `summarize_*`, and
`build_het_core.py` — into `scripts/analysis/`. The directory partly exists: the
five analysis `.mk` fragments were relocated there by ticket 0239. Only Tier-3
entry points (per the 0254 audit) move; imported library modules stay flat, as do
the semantic-phase exceptions.

This move is the real prerequisite for `0241` (the five SPLIT extractions land in
the phase subdirs this ticket creates) — 0241 is re-pointed to Blocked-by this
ticket, not the tracker.

## Depends on 0253 + 0254
- `0253` installs the relative source-root path model (subdir imports resolve).
- `0254` publishes the Tier-2/Tier-3 list — the contract for what moves.

## Semantic-phase exceptions (architecture.md § "Phase is semantic")
- `compute_reranker_calibration.py` is Phase-1 (harvest), NOT analysis — it does
  not move here (handled by 0256's harvest scope / stays flat per the audit).
- Any `compute_*`/`summarize_*` the 0254 audit flagged as imported stays flat
  (e.g. an extracted `summarize_core_venues` library part).

## Relevant files
- `scripts/analyze_*.py`, `scripts/compute_*.py`, `scripts/summarize_*.py`, `scripts/build_het_core.py`
- `scripts/analysis/` — already holds the analysis `.mk` fragments (0239)
- `docs/repo-layout.md` — Tier-2/Tier-3 audit table (0254)
- `Makefile` + `scripts/analysis/*.mk` — analysis target script paths to repoint

## Actions
1. `git mv` each Tier-3 analysis entry point into `scripts/analysis/`.
2. Repoint every Make target script path to the new location.
3. Leave Tier-2 library modules and semantic-phase exceptions flat.

## Test
- `make -n` for one analysis target yields the same prereq graph — only the path
  segment changes.
- Moved entry points import + run under `PYTHONPATH=scripts:libs/openalex-corpus/src`.
- `make check` green; analysis outputs byte-identical before/after (pure move).

## Invariants
- Only Tier-3 entry points move; Tier-2 modules + semantic exceptions stay flat.
- No top-level `src/`; no `python -m`; flat module names unchanged.
- Layering (architecture.md rule 4): a compute module never imports a plotter.
- One logical move per PR (this ticket = the analysis move only).

## Exit criteria
- All Tier-3 `analyze_*`/`compute_*`/`summarize_*`/`build_het_core` entry points
  under `scripts/analysis/`.
- Every Make script path repointed; no dangling reference.
- `make check` and `make clean && make all` green; outputs byte-identical.

